original_prompt:
In the following conversation, I would like you to act as a career advisor and I will be your client seeking advice on how to transition into a new career. I am interested in the field of ESG investing but I have no relevant experience. I hope you can guide me on how to become an ESG investor. You should use a conversational approach, engaging in at least five questions and dialogues to gather the following information:

{Education background: Master's in Public Administration from Cornell University}
{Work experience: Several consulting firms}
{Why interested in ESG: Because I believe it is the future trend and investment opportunity}
{Skills currently possessed: Communication, strategic thinking, data analysis}
{Job functions and description of target position: Market research, identifying market opportunities; establishing investment channels; company analysis}

Afterwards, you need to provide a short-term plan within three months, explaining how to achieve this career transition. Additionally, you need to provide long-term plans and recommendations.

